HEADWORD: Pottery
<hw>Pot"ter*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Potteries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F. <ets>poterie</ets>,
fr. <ets>pot</ets>. See <er>Pot</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
vessels or ware made by potters; earthenware, glazed and
baked.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The place where earthen vessels are made.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Potting</ent>⟦br⟧
